Patch Set 3:

Yeah, Luid mostly with respect to adding IDE specific file types to ignore. I need to be more updated about what's the community take on it in general however, remember Venkatesh mentioning that one of his patches was not accepted once.

May be this will change the stance!

Patch Set 3:

Hi Nikhil,

Thanks for the prompt response.

I see, yeah I think it is up to each project. For example, nova, heat, oslo-incubator, oslo.config, and cinder have accepted similar changes, but neutron did not. 

In general I think it's a helpful change that makes it easier for those developers that use Eclipse, or other IDEs, and it doesn't really affect those that don't since the change is completely invisible to them.

Here are some sample changes from other projects:
https://github.com/openstack/nova/commit/6c1d7989d9bf4aea16758542e203cbbad2f7c6f0
https://github.com/openstack/nova/commit/a577fc5f778731fcd1a7d9f2c0a216ffad6eb0c0
